What to Build (views.py)
You must implement four kinds of views.

In the notes/notes.txt, indicate name of view for each specific type and its purpose.

You can have as many views as you want of these four kinds depending on your project needs.

I will grade it based on implementation of atleast one.

The one which you will mark for grading should be attached to a working URL.



A) Function-Based Views (2)


View 1: HttpResponse (Manual)

Return raw HTML as a string OR

Load a template manually using loader.get_template()

Wrap result in HttpResponse



View 2: render() (Shortcut)

Query your model (e.g., Model.objects.all())

Pass queryset into a context dictionary

Return a rendered template using render()

B) Class-Based Views (2)


View 3: Base CBV (inherit from View)

Inherit from django.views import View

Implement get() (or post() if you prefer)

Manually query your model (Model.objects.all() etc.)

Return a rendered template with context



View 4: Generic CBV (inherit from Django generic views)

Implement as many as you want:

ListView

DetailView

UpdateView
Delete View
or any other options of your preference


Requirements:

Use model = YourModel

Either follow Django default template naming conventions or set template_name

Optional but encouraged: set context_object_name

